dct_description_sm: from a trigonometrical survey under the direction of A.D. Bache, Superintendent of the Survey of the Coast of the United States ; triangulation by R.D. Cutts, Asst. ; topography by R.D. Cutts, Asst. and A.F. Rodgers, Sub-Asst. ; hydrography by the party under the command of Comdr. James Alden, U.S.N.
Oriented with north toward upper left.
Relief shown by hachures; depths shown by soundings.
From: "Report of the Superintendent of the Coast Survey for 1857," Senate Ex. Doc. no. 33, 35th Cong., 1st sess.-932.
